snippet.textDisplay:
Sack Ole now, and the energy of the squad disappears and we'll forever regret sacking him, because those kids won't be able to recover from emotional pains for a manager that has given them his best. Ole has made those kids believe in themselves and worked so hard. I feel they're playing for the love of the manager and not the club anymore.
Pochettino will fail woefully with this squad. He had a better squad at Tottenham and gave them nothing. Poch can not endure the pain Ole is facing with a sick board. Let the fans back Ole. Injuries haven't made it any easier though, but Ole needs time and support from the board and fans. Forget about the history of this club for now and let this rebuild continue irrespective of the pain. Ole has tried to manage what he has.
In conclusion, knowing that the manager is not the problem, why make a move to sack the present manager when the problem has not been solved? Won't subsequent managers face the same challenge??
